## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of job in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Job is the bounded institutional role structure
through which function,
responsibility,
authority,
expected capability,
and accountability
become meaningful.

Job is not identical to skill or work.
Skill is capability,
work is execution flow,
and job is the structured role
within which duties and authority are recognized.

## architectural_position
Job sits between:
- organization/company role topology
- work assignment
- skill expectations
- authority boundary
- review and accountability

## required_behavior
- job identity must remain explicit
- duty and responsibility scope must remain explicit
- authority scope must remain explicit
- current and historical job states must remain distinguishable
- job must not imply unrestricted actor authority

## canonical_rules
- job assignment does not imply unlimited discretion
- job and skill meanings must remain distinct
- historical job assignment must remain queryable
- ambiguous job authority fails closed

## state_model
The job domain distinguishes:
- proposed job
- active job
- restricted job
- transformed job
- closed job
- historical job

## actor_boundary
- job holder
- assigning authority
- reviewer
- operator
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if job identity is unclear, stop job-sensitive paths
- if duty/authority scope is unclear, fail closed
- if job changes, preserve assignment history
- if job closes, preserve historical role trace

## review_checklist
- job identity is explicit
- duty/authority scope is explicit
- skill/job distinction is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
